0. To start the SSH setup for github, Follow the basic steps found here:  https://docs.github.com/en/authentication/connecting-to-github-with-ssh

To Clone an existing repository:

1. Select the Repository in Github (click on it)
2. Click in "Code"
3. In the "Local" panel that will open, make sure you click "SSH"
4. Click the "Copy" icon (or copy ithe url using control+c) to copy the url information, which should be similar to "git@github.com:<user>/<repository name>.git"
5. From your work station, type "git clone git@github.com:<user>/<repository name>.git"

From this point, the local (clone) repository should be connected to the remote github, and pulls and pushes will be using the ssh keys configured in step 0.

To create a new repository

1. I usualy create the repository using the Github web interface
2. Then follow the cloning steps above.


